Police in the Eastern Cape are investigating a case of murder after five people were gunned down in a shack in Bethelsdorp on Saturday night. Other than the fact that the incident occurred in Mistletoe Road in Extension 33 in Bethelsdorp no further details were immediately available. Police have appealed to members of the local community members to assist them in their investigation into the killings and help track down the suspects. Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share